  "text": "Granulosa cell ADRP protein levels showed a similar pattern. Monkey granulosa cell lysates subjected to Western blotting for ADRP yielded a single band at approximately 50 kDa, consistent with the expected size for ADRP [CITATION_1] ; tubulin was also detected as a single band of approximately 50 kDa (Fig. 3A) . ADRP protein levels were low or nondetectable before (0 h) hCG administration; low levels were present 12 h after hCG administration, intermediate levels were present 24 h after hCG, and the highest levels were observed 36 h after administration of hCG (Fig. 3B) .",
